newsitem.title: LUXEMBOURG: Cargolux traffic up nine pct in Sept.
newsitem.headline: Cargolux traffic up nine pct in Sept.

text.p: Cargolux Airlines International said it flew 176.7 million freight tonne kilometres (FTK) in September 1996, up nine percent in the same month last year.
In the first nine months of 1996, the Luxembourg-based cargo airline flew a total of 1.45 billion FTK, an increase of four percent on 1995 levels.
Cargolux operates a fleet of three Boeing 747-400Fs and three 747-200Fs as well as an additional 747-200F on leaseback.
Cargolux recently concluded an agreement with Boeing bringing forward an order for a fourth 747-400 from September 1998 to August 1997. - Air Cargo Newsroom Tel+44 171 542-7706 Fax+44 171 542-5017
